delete files except source files : make clean
    NOTE: all files whose name matches '*.log' will be deleted!

compile moecompiler : make -j4 opti="-O2" compiler
compile moecompiler and run : make -j4 opti="-O2" run args="testcase.sysy -S -o testcase.s"
run directly : ./compiler testcase.sysy -S -o testcase.s

usage ./compiler input.sysy [-d] -l/-p/-s/-i/-S/-s<submain> -o output.s [-O1]

command line options :
    The second argument (i.e. argv[1]) will be interpreted as input file path.
    (For now, compiler is designed to compile one file for once)
    
    [-d] : debug option
        /*  This option will enable debug information to be created.
         *  This will also enable default mdb which prints information to stdout. 
         */
    -l/-p/-s/-i/-S/-f<submain> : compiler option
        [-l] : lexer option
            /*  Process input file until lexical analyze finished.
             *  Token streams will be output to output file.
             */
        [-S] : assemble option
            /*  Assemble file.
             * */
        [-s] : sub funtion
            /*  Invoke sub function provided.
             *  */
        [-f<submain>] : unittest function invoke
            /*  use 
             *  */
            suported:
                listall : see all sub mains.
    -o<out file path> : specify output file path.

    -O1 : opitmization

example :
    test lexer : make -j4 opti="-O2" args="testDir/test.sysy -d -f lexerTest -o "testDir/test.tokens"

